headline: Regional Bank Stocks Aren’t Out of the Woods Yet. Why It’s Time to Lighten Up.
summary: The market is betting that the credit concerns that hit  Zions Bancorp  and Western Alliance will fade.  If it’s wrong, select bank stocks could slump again.  Bank stocks started to drop last week when  JPMorgan Chase  revealed a $170 million hit from the bankruptcy of Tricolor, a small auto lender, leading CEO Jamie Dimon to muse that “when you see one cockroach, there are probably more.”
